Looking at them, I think...

491
00:28:55,839 --> 00:28:56,839
they wouldn't dare to do anything.

492
00:28:57,599 --> 00:28:58,640
Okay.

493
00:28:59,039 --> 00:29:00,119
I'll keep an eye on them.

494
00:29:00,279 --> 00:29:01,279
You stay alert too.

495
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:02,759
Don't worry.

496
00:29:11,279 --> 00:29:13,039
Aren't you unruly?

497
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,799
Why are you so useless?

498
00:29:15,279 --> 00:29:17,200
This guy seems like a real fighter.

499
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:18,759
We'd better stay out of his sight.

500
00:29:18,759 --> 00:29:20,000
Do I need your advice?

501
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:22,359
- I... - Don't talk back.

502
00:29:23,079 --> 00:29:24,240
I'm telling you.

503
00:29:24,799 --> 00:29:26,480
We'll let him go this time.

504
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,799
Okay?

505
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,240
Go.

506
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:39,240
Hello.

507
00:29:40,519 --> 00:29:41,559
They've left the hotel.

508
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:42,839
It's okay.

509
00:29:42,839 --> 00:29:43,920
Copy that.

510
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:01,599
Let's talk after the party is over.

511
00:30:04,119 --> 00:30:06,119
You are always so cheerful.

512
00:30:06,119 --> 00:30:07,519
I didn't know you're so reliable in handling matters.

513
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:10,519
You don't know me at all.

514
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:12,480
I can't deny that.

515
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:17,599
I'm sure you're just like most people.

516
00:30:18,359 --> 00:30:23,480
You think I'm bossy, capricious,

517
00:30:23,799 --> 00:30:26,279
unreasonable, and arrogant.

518
00:30:26,400 --> 00:30:27,640
That's how you see me.

519
00:30:27,759 --> 00:30:28,839
Don't laugh.

520
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:32,000
I know that's what you have in mind.

521
00:30:32,599 --> 00:30:35,000
But what I really want to tell you is...

522
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:38,079
that's just a way...

523
00:30:38,079 --> 00:30:39,680
to protect myself.

524
00:30:41,119 --> 00:30:44,000
It's not necessarily the real me.

525
00:30:44,599 --> 00:30:48,599
Today, I decided to sit down...

526
00:30:48,599 --> 00:30:49,599
and tell you about this...

527
00:30:49,599 --> 00:30:51,759
in a serious manner because...

528
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,480
It's because...

529
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:57,160
I want to ask if you could give me a chance...

530
00:30:58,039 --> 00:30:59,799
I mean, give us a chance...

531
00:31:00,319 --> 00:31:03,440
to know each other better.

532
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,200
When you suddenly act like this,

533
00:31:14,759 --> 00:31:15,839
I'm not used to it.

534
00:31:23,119 --> 00:31:24,119
Chen Chen.

535
00:31:26,079 --> 00:31:27,240
Recently,

536
00:31:28,599 --> 00:31:30,160
I confessed to a woman...

537
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:32,279
in front of so many people.

538
00:31:33,839 --> 00:31:35,400
I told her I really like her.

539
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:38,160
And deep down, I love her too.

540
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:43,759
And I still haven't heard back from her.

541
00:31:43,759 --> 00:31:44,960
Until now,

542
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:47,279
I'm still holding on.

543
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,119
I'm still holding on.

544
00:31:49,599 --> 00:31:51,160
I will persevere.

545
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:53,200
It's that woman, right?

546
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,200
I lost to her, again.

547
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,400
Let me ask you something.

548
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:11,720
What if, in the end,

549
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:15,240
she still won't agree to it?

550
00:32:18,119 --> 00:32:21,440
Will you continue to fight?

551
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:24,680
Or would you choose someone else?

552
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:26,880
I'll hang in there.

553
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:41,960
Then I...

554
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,279
I wish you happiness.

555
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:48,920
We're buddies from now on.

556
00:32:49,839 --> 00:32:50,920
Thank you.

557
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:53,079
Don't even mention it.

558
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:07,480
I got rejected for the first time in my life.

559
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:10,680
It's tough.

560
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:14,160
Give me a friendly hug.

561
00:33:20,680 --> 00:33:22,960
Forget about the hug.

562
00:33:24,279 --> 00:33:25,880
I'm wearing a white suit after all.

563
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,279
What white suit?

564
00:33:27,279 --> 00:33:29,039
That's just an excuse!

565
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,119
Why can't you be nicer to me?

566
00:33:31,319 --> 00:33:32,599
What's going on?

567
00:33:32,599 --> 00:33:34,240
What are you doing?

568
00:33:34,559 --> 00:33:35,599
Here.

569
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,720
I'm deeply regretting what I did.

570
00:33:43,519 --> 00:33:44,759
I'll take any punishment.

571
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:48,079
Serves you right.

572
00:33:48,599 --> 00:33:49,720
How shameless.

573
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:14,480
Things went so well for the opening party,

574
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:16,960
all thanks to you.

575
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,000
Don't say that.

576
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:20,769
Thanks to everyone.

577
00:34:22,239 --> 00:34:24,329
Can we be more friendly to each other?

578
00:34:25,039 --> 00:34:26,199
I'm friendly to you.

579
00:34:32,519 --> 00:34:33,679
I'm happy...

580
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:36,289
that I got to work with you.

581
00:34:37,079 --> 00:34:38,119
What about you?

582
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:41,199
I'm happy too.

583
00:34:43,119 --> 00:34:44,159
Actually,

584
00:34:45,639 --> 00:34:47,519
I was waiting for the right time...

585
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:51,360
and trying to look for a special way.

586
00:34:52,809 --> 00:34:53,809
But then I thought...

587
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,599
when exactly is the right time.

588
00:34:57,519 --> 00:34:58,920
You know, when it comes to the right person,

589
00:35:01,769 --> 00:35:03,639
the present is the best time.

590
00:35:14,400 --> 00:35:15,440
Marry me.

591
00:35:17,599 --> 00:35:18,639
Lan Qi.

592
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,360
This is too sudden.

593
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,559
You are not surprised.

594
00:35:31,039 --> 00:35:32,119
Yes, it's too sudden.

595
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,360
I know you care about me.

596
00:35:37,119 --> 00:35:38,119
You care about my parents too.

597
00:35:39,159 --> 00:35:40,239
But...

598
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,329
I can't go on like this.

599
00:35:52,519 --> 00:35:54,400
I must admit that at first,

600
00:35:56,239 --> 00:35:57,329
I hired you as my bodyguard...

601
00:35:57,329 --> 00:35:59,639
not because I wanted you to protect me.

602
00:35:59,639 --> 00:36:01,440
Neither that nor offering you...

603
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:03,400
a well-paying job.

604
00:36:04,289 --> 00:36:07,000
I want us to spend more time together.

605
00:36:09,599 --> 00:36:11,119
I think if I have enough time,

606
00:36:13,809 --> 00:36:15,289
I can make you love me again.

607
00:36:15,289 --> 00:36:17,119
I could really get through to you.

608
00:36:17,119 --> 00:36:18,360
But now,

609
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:21,559
I can't get in.

610
00:36:24,599 --> 00:36:26,440
Because there's already someone in there, isn't there?

611
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:28,960
That's right.

612
00:36:31,519 --> 00:36:32,519
I can't lie to you.

613
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,639
I can't lie to myself either.

614
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:38,000
Does he...

615
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,329
Does he treat you better than I do?

616
00:36:43,119 --> 00:36:44,119
You are nice.

617
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,960
You are the perfect candidate for a husband.

618
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,809
It doesn't matter who you end up with,

619
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,880
you always make sure to keep your lives in order.

620
00:36:56,769 --> 00:36:58,159
But love isn't a competition.

621
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,440
It's not a competition about who fits who better...

622
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:04,440
or who treats who better.

623
00:37:12,639 --> 00:37:13,920
What are you doing?

624
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:19,440
Get rid of the evidence. It's embarrassing.

625
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,679
Pretend this never happened.

626
00:37:27,769 --> 00:37:29,079
He didn't win and I didn't lose.

627
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,079
Do you feel much better?

628
00:37:39,719 --> 00:37:40,809
Thank you.

629
00:37:48,559 --> 00:37:49,639
All right.

630
00:37:51,119 --> 00:37:53,159
That's the end of personal stuff.

631
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:55,599
Please don't tell anyone.

632
00:37:55,920 --> 00:37:57,079
Show some respect to your boss.

633
00:37:58,809 --> 00:38:00,000
As for work,

634
00:38:01,239 --> 00:38:03,480
do you want to leave or stay?

635
00:38:04,239 --> 00:38:05,289
It's your call.

636
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,000
No matter what,

637
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:12,769
we'll be friends forever.

638
00:38:32,119 --> 00:38:33,159
It's a big deal.

639
00:38:33,159 --> 00:38:34,559
Why didn't you tell us?

640
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,159
Even if I did, the ending would still be the same.

641
00:38:41,329 --> 00:38:42,639
How is he not a good fit?

642
00:38:43,039 --> 00:38:44,239
What's wrong with Lan Qi?

643
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,199
He is great,

644
00:38:49,639 --> 00:38:51,039
but I don't have feelings for him.

645
00:38:51,239 --> 00:38:53,480
No one would have feelings for another person all of a sudden.

646
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,960
Even married couples have to adjust to each other.

647
00:38:56,159 --> 00:38:57,159
Look at me and your mom.

648
00:38:57,769 --> 00:38:59,199
Don't remind me.

649
00:38:59,639 --> 00:39:01,480
We were happy, right?

650
00:39:01,599 --> 00:39:02,840
You have to admit that.

651
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,559
There are more bad days. You should admit it too.

652
00:39:09,519 --> 00:39:11,880
Okay, back at me, you two.

653
00:39:13,769 --> 00:39:17,289
Lan Qi and I didn't break up...

654
00:39:17,599 --> 00:39:19,039
because we never started.

655
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,119
Shi Yi, tell me the truth.

656
00:39:22,119 --> 00:39:23,599
Is it because of Hou Jue?

657
00:39:23,599 --> 00:39:24,809
Hou Jue?

658
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,559
Him again?

659
00:39:28,599 --> 00:39:31,000
Whatever you say.

660
00:39:31,559 --> 00:39:33,559
But Hou Jue is very different from him.

661
00:39:33,559 --> 00:39:34,920
At least he's real.

662
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:37,519
He never hides his pros and cons.

663
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,159
At least it's easier...

664
00:39:39,519 --> 00:39:40,679
dealing with people like him.

665
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:41,920
Have you ever thought...

666
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:44,440
you might never be able to meet someone better than Lan Qi?

667
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:45,519
That's right.

668
00:39:46,159 --> 00:39:47,599
That's what you think.

669
00:39:47,920 --> 00:39:49,679
I just want to find someone I like.

670
00:39:49,679 --> 00:39:52,159
You used to like Zhu Da Peng.

671
00:39:52,159 --> 00:39:53,559
Yes, that's right.

672
00:39:53,769 --> 00:39:55,880
But it's because you liked him.

673
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:57,639
You thought I should get married at this age.

674
00:39:57,639 --> 00:39:59,199
You thought he was a good catch.

675
00:39:59,199 --> 00:40:01,199
We somehow ended up together.

676
00:40:01,960 --> 00:40:03,289
I didn't figure out...

677
00:40:03,289 --> 00:40:04,559
what was wrong with me that time.

678
00:40:05,039 --> 00:40:06,719
Are you sure you know what are you doing now?

679
00:40:06,719 --> 00:40:07,880
Yes, I know it well.

680
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:10,519
Whether I marry or not or regardless of whom I marry,

681
00:40:10,519 --> 00:40:11,920
I want to choose what I like...

682
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,079
on my own.

683
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:15,400
It's my life.

684
00:40:24,159 --> 00:40:25,159
Shi Yi.

685
00:40:26,039 --> 00:40:27,329
You'll be 30 years old soon.

686
00:40:28,559 --> 00:40:30,159
I don't think you can get married.

687
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:32,559
When no one wants you anymore,

688
00:40:32,809 --> 00:40:35,639
the three of us don't have to live separately.

689
00:40:36,199 --> 00:40:38,440
You're both living with me.

690
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,639
Let's live together.

691
00:40:39,809 --> 00:40:40,809
You are so kind.

692
00:40:42,679 --> 00:40:45,360
Thank you. I've been alone for over a decade.

693
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:46,440
I'm so used to it.

694
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,360
That's a forced habit.

695
00:40:49,289 --> 00:40:50,480
As the expert said,

696
00:40:51,159 --> 00:40:53,039
one doesn't know what to eat when they live alone.

697
00:40:53,039 --> 00:40:54,639
That's the dilemma of the century.

698
00:40:55,719 --> 00:40:57,039
It's much better when two people live together.

699
00:40:57,159 --> 00:40:58,599
The expert's surname is Wu, right?

700
00:40:58,840 --> 00:40:59,960
Don't doubt it.

701
00:41:00,079 --> 00:41:01,119
Don't flatter yourself.

702
00:41:02,199 --> 00:41:03,199
Shi Yi.

703
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:04,440
Your dad and I think...

704
00:41:04,440 --> 00:41:06,239
you will be happy if you marry Lan Qi.

705
00:41:06,239 --> 00:41:07,480
Your mom is right.

706
00:41:07,719 --> 00:41:10,559
But happiness is up to you.

707
00:41:10,719 --> 00:41:11,840
Stay single if you want.

708
00:41:12,039 --> 00:41:13,039
It's no big deal.

709
00:41:13,239 --> 00:41:15,599
Why did you change your mind?

710
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:19,840
I thought it would be hard to explain.

711
00:41:19,840 --> 00:41:21,000
It makes sense right away.

712
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,639
Mom, you are so wise.

713
00:41:22,639 --> 00:41:23,809
Here, have some shrimp.

714
00:41:23,809 --> 00:41:24,920
Okay.

715
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:25,960
Shi Yi.

716
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:27,119
Have some vegetables too.

717
00:41:27,119 --> 00:41:28,239
- Eat some vegetables and meat. - I'm telling you.

718
00:41:28,519 --> 00:41:29,639
I don't want to come back...

719
00:41:30,039 --> 00:41:31,239
to this restaurant again.

720
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,329
It reminds me of the hard feelings.

721
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:36,599
I think I need to order more food for you.

722
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:38,480
Excuse me.

723
00:41:38,679 --> 00:41:39,679
We would like to order more.

724
00:41:40,559 --> 00:41:41,559
Eat up.

725
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:43,559
Hello, what would you like to order?